org.stekikun.dolmen.syntax

Class Lexer.Entry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.stekikun.dolmen.syntax.Lexer.Entry
  • Enclosing class:
    Lexer

    public static final class Lexer.Entry
extends Object
    A lexer rule entry is a sequence of regular expressions associated to semantic actions. A rule has a name, a return type and may have some arguments. The regular expressions that form the rule are called the clauses and are normally interpreted with the longest match priority, unless specified otherwise.

    NB: In state-based lexer generators like JLex or JavaCC, the equivalent of a lexer rule entry is a lexer state along with all the rules that apply to this state. The equivalent of changing lexer state when matching a regular expression is to call the corresponding rule in the semantic action.
